### Phase 3.5 — Cross-Collection Linking (NER-based)

Design agreed 2026-06-18. Build after full dataset ingestion and all file types verified.

**Architecture:**
- Tag chunks with shared entity references at ingest time (not query time)
- NER approach: pattern matching + keyword scan against live Postgres entity dictionary (self-building)
- Validated against actual collection values — no hardcoding of specific names
- Tags stored in chunk payload permanently (e.g. `recon_refs`, `fix_tag_refs`)
- Query time: O(1) payload lookup → fetch linked records → Stage 3 unified synthesis

**Entity types to recognize:**
- Recon filenames (`gsact.txt` etc.) → validated against `recon_assist_file.identifier`
- PB filenames → validated against `recon_assist_file.aliases`
- Client/broker names (Goldman etc.) → validated against `recon_assist_file.type` + `primary_name`
- Tidal job names → validated against `recon_assist_file.primary_name`
- FIX tags → validated against `xml_test.identifier`

**Config:** `config/cross_links.json` — defines source/target collection pairs, ref_field name,
and match_fields (pattern-based or keyword-based). `keyword:true` entries build entity dictionary
from live Postgres values at ingest time — self-building, always current.

**Also in this phase — FIX message interpretation (text input):**
User pastes raw FIX message text → system parses tag=value pairs, looks up each tag in xml_test,
composes plain English summary ("This is an Execution Report, qty=500, price=102.50...").
Text input version buildable now. Image input needs vision model (Phase 5.M7).

**Also in this phase — Missing file check:**
User pastes list of filenames that arrived OK; system returns files in recon collection NOT in
the list, with key details. Implement in Chat tab (not Streamlit widget). Uses Postgres NOT IN
query against identifier + aliases fields.

**Prerequisites before building:**
- Full dataset ingestion complete (all file types, all collections)
- All smoke tests passing on full datasets

